claim.claim-text:
1. A surgical port feature comprising:
a port feature body comprising a top surface, a bottom surface, and an outer sidewall that extends between the top and the bottom surfaces;
a first channel that extends in a first direction straight from the top surface to the bottom surface;
a second channel that extends in a second direction straight from the top surface to the bottom surface; and
an electrically conductive path that extends from the outer sidewall to an inner wall portion of at least one of the first channel and the second channel, wherein the electrically conductive path is disposed relative to less electrically conductive portions of the port feature body to provide a predefined electrically conductive path through the port feature body to an electrical ground;
wherein the first and second directions are different from one another.

12. The surgical port feature of claim 1 further comprising:
a seal positioned in the first channel;
wherein the seal is integrally molded with the port feature body.

31. The surgical port feature of claim 28, wherein the port feature further comprises:
a seal positioned in at least one of the first channel and the second channel;
wherein the electrically conductive path comprises at least a portion of the seal.
